WITH_TRA ~Xan/%s/BO#XAN.tra~ BEGIN
  OUTER_SET strref2 = RESOLVE_STR_REF(@0)
  /* Dynaheir... Khalid... Imoen... (sigh) I am sorry to hear of your past misfortunes. Do you have the slightest idea of what your captor wanted? */
END

WITH_TRA ~Xan/%s/BO#XAN.tra~ BEGIN
  OUTER_SET strref3 = RESOLVE_STR_REF(@2174)
  /* Why do you treat these matters so lightly? You buried Gorion; Khalid and Dynaheir died practically before your eyes. Your mother is likely dead, too. Do not jest with death, <CHARNAME>. */
END

WITH_TRA ~Xan/%s/BO#XAN.tra~ BEGIN
  OUTER_SET strref4 = RESOLVE_STR_REF(@2201)
  /* Nothing good would have come of it, in any case. Should it have come to pass, Irenicus would have only gloated a little longer before killing me instead of the unfortunate Khalid. */
END

WITH_TRA ~Xan/%s/BO#XAN.tra~ BEGIN
  OUTER_SET strref5 = RESOLVE_STR_REF(@2417)
  /* Yes, my infatuation with you is ridiculous. You are a dangerous woman to travel with, let alone to care about. I doubted it before, but poor Khalid's and Dynaheir's fates proved it to me well enough. You are one of Bhaal's progeny, a manifestation of murder, a symbol of ultimate destruction. Mine. */
END

